  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "My car back glass has been broken, how can I claim United India insurance?",
  "response": "To claim insurance from United India Insurance for your broken car back glass, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Notify the Insurer Immediately**: Contact United India Insurance as soon as possible to report the incident. You can call their customer service or visit their website to find the appropriate contact information.\n\n2. **File a Police Report (If Necessary)**: If the breakage was due to an accident, vandalism, or theft, file a police report. This will be required by the insurance company as part of the claims process.\n\n3. **Gather Necessary Documentation**: Prepare the following documents:\n   - Duly filled and signed claim form (available on the United India Insurance website or at their office).\n   - Copy of the insurance policy.\n   - FIR (First Information Report) from the police, if applicable.\n   - Repair estimate from an authorized service center.\n   - Photographs of the damage.\n   - Any other documents requested by the insurer.\n\n4. **Submit the Claim**: Submit the claim form along with the supporting documents to United India Insurance. This can usually be done online through their website or in person at one of their offices.\n\n5. **Vehicle Inspection**: The insurance company may send a surveyor to inspect the damage to your vehicle. Cooperate fully during this inspection.\n\n6. **Repair Your Vehicle**: Once the claim is approved, you can proceed with the repairs. Use an authorized service center as specified by the insurance company to ensure your claim is processed smoothly.\n\n7. **Claim Settlement**: After the repairs are completed, submit the final bills and any other required documents to the insurance company. They will process the claim and reimburse you according to the terms of your policy.\n\n8. **Follow Up**: Keep in touch with the insurance company to ensure your claim is being processed and to address any issues that may arise.\n\nRemember to read your policy document carefully to understand the coverage, any deductibles, and the process specific to your policy. If you have any questions, don't hesitate to contact United India Insurance for clarification.",
